本片获得了许多积极的评价。它最初在戛纳电影节上获得的反响褒贬不一。在戛纳的首次放映后，本片获得了影评人8到11分钟的起立鼓掌<ref>{{cite web|url=http://backseatcuddler.com/2009/05/20/inglourious-basterds-gets-8-minute-standing-ovation-at-cannes/|title=Inglourious Basterds Gets 8 Minute Standing Ovation|publisher=Backseatcuddler.com|date=2009-05-20|accessdate=January 18, 2010<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nEAs27PD |archivedate=February 1, 2010 -->|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120710143140/http://backseatcuddler.com/2009/05/20/inglourious-basterds-gets-8-minute-standing-ovation-at-cannes/|archive-date=2012-07-10|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theinsider.com/news/2194255__Inglourious_Basterds_Debuts_to_Standing_Ovation|title=Inglourious Basterds Debuts To Standing Ovation|work=The Insider|publisher=[[CBS_Interactive|CBS Interactive]]|date=2009-05-20|accessdate=January 18, 2010<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nEAwvedV |archivedate=February 1, 2010 -->|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100117163234/http://www.theinsider.com/news/2194255__Inglourious_Basterds_Debuts_to_Standing_Ovation|archive-date=2010-01-17|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。而法国的著名报刊《[[世界报_(法国)|世界报]]》则不欣赏它，写道：“塔伦蒂诺迷失在虚构的二战中。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/festival-de-cannes/article/2009/05/21/inglourious-basterds-tarantino-s-egare-dans-une-seconde-guerre-mondiale-fictive_1196062_766360.html|title="Inglourious Basterds" Tarantino wanders in a fictional World War II|work=[[Le_Monde|Le Monde]]|publisher=La Vie-Le Monde|language=fr|date=2009-05-21|accessdate=July 1, 2009<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nEApBG9c |archivedate=February 1, 2010 -->|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090522012957/http://www.lemonde.fr/festival-de-cannes/article/2009/05/21/inglourious-basterds-tarantino-s-egare-dans-une-seconde-guerre-mondiale-fictive_1196062_766360.html|archive-date=2009-05-22|dead-url=yes}}</ref>”除此之外，《[[綜藝_(雜誌)|综艺]]》杂志的安妮·汤普森（{{lang|en|Anne Thompson}}）赞扬了本片，但认为它不算一部杰作，说：“《无耻混蛋》很具有观赏性，但不完全很有魅力……你不会以一种特别的方式进入电影中的世界，而是保持一定距离地观看，欣赏其中的指涉和出色的镜头语言（{{lang|fr|mise en scène}}）。这是一部最好看第二遍的电影。<ref>{{cite news | author=Thompson, Anne | title=Tarantino's Inglourious Basterds Plays Cannes | url=http://weblogs.variety.com/thompsononhollywood/2009/05/tarantinos-inglourious-basterds-plays-cannes.html | work=[[Variety_(magazine)|Variety]] | publisher=[[Reed_Business_Information|Reed Business Information]] | date=2009-05-20 | accessdate=May 21, 2009<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nEB1UCMg |archivedate=February 1, 2010 --> | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090523095007/http://weblogs.variety.com/thompsononhollywood/2009/05/tarantinos-inglourious-basterds-plays-cannes.html | archive-date=2009-05-23 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>”影评人{{link-en|詹姆斯·贝拉迪内利|James Berardinelli}}给了本片他2009年的第一篇四星评论，认为“《无耻混蛋》是昆汀·塔伦蒂诺自《低俗小说》后最好的作品”，它“观看起来非常享受”<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reelviews.net/php_review_template.php?identifier=1774|title=Inglourious Basterds Movie Review|work=Reelviews.net|publisher=[[James_Berardinelli|James Berardinelli]]|date=2009-08-18|accessdate=January 19, 2010<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nEB4Bvcf |archivedate=February 1, 2010 -->|archive-date=2010-02-01|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5nEB4Bvcf?url=http://www.reelviews.net/php_review_template.php?identifier=1774|dead-url=no}}</ref>。《[[芝加哥太陽報|芝加哥太陽報]]》的[[羅傑·艾伯特|羅傑·艾伯特]]也给了本片四星的评论，写道：“昆汀·塔伦蒂诺的《无耻混蛋》是一部宏大、冒失、大胆的战争片，会使一些人恼怒，令其他人吃惊，展示了他的真才实学，他是一个带来狂想式愉悦的导演。<ref>{{cite news | author=Ebert, Roger | authorlink=Roger Ebert | title=Review: Inglourious Basterds | url=http://rogerebert.suntimes.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20090819/REVIEWS/908199995 | work=[[Chicago_Sun-Times|Chicago Sun-Times]] | publisher=RogerEbert.com | date=2009-08-20 | accessdate=August 20, 2009<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nEBCMCku | archivedate=February 1, 2010 --> | archive-date=2010-02-01 | archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5nEBCMCku?url=http://rogerebert.suntimes.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=%2F20090819%2FREVIEWS%2F908199995 | dead-url=no }}</ref>”作家和评论家{{link-en|丹尼尔·曼德尔森|Daniel_Mendelsohn}}为描绘美籍犹太人的方式感到困扰，片中美籍犹太人模仿了德国人对欧洲犹太人的暴行，他指出：“在《无耻混蛋》中，塔伦蒂诺沉溺于复仇的暴力快感中，把犹太人变成了纳粹。<ref>{{cite web | author=Mendelsohn, Daniel | title=Review: 'Inglourious Basterds': When Jews Attack | url=http://www.newsweek.com/id/212016/page/2 | work=[[Newsweek|Newsweek]] | publisher=[[The_Washington_Post_Company|The Washington Post Company]] | date=2009-08-14 | accessdate=August 21, 2009 <!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nFhc0HC9 | archivedate=February 2, 2010 --> | archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5nFhc0HC9?url=http://www.newsweek.com/id/212016/page/2 | archive-date=2010-02-02 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>”《[[衛報|衛報]]》的{{link-en|彼得·布拉德肖|Peter Bradshaw}}说自己“因它糟糕得令人生气，非常让人失望而遭到了打击”<ref>{{cite news |first=Peter |last=Bradshaw |authorlink=Peter Bradshaw |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/2009/aug/19/inglourious-basterds-review-brad-pitt-quentin-tarantino |title=Film review: Inglourious Basterds |work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian_Media_Group|Guardian Media Group]] |date=2009-09-19 |accessdate=August 20, 2009<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nFhnaSqF | archivedate=February 2, 2010 --> |location=London |archive-date=2013-06-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130625060324/http://www.guardian.co.uk/film/2009/aug/19/inglourious-basterds-review-brad-pitt-quentin-tarantino |dead-url=no }}</ref>。《[[紐約客|紐約客]]》的{{link-en|大卫·丹拜|David Denby}}尽管称赞了克里斯托弗·瓦尔兹的表演（“美国观众不熟悉的好演员”），但对电影持负面评价：“该电影的制作技巧不错，但它太愚蠢了以至于无法被享受，甚至把它当做一个笑话来看都是如此。[……]塔伦蒂诺已经变成了一个尴尬的存在：他在电影方面的幼稚愚蠢（{{lang|fr|idiot de la cinémathèque}}）盖过了他在制作影像方面的高超技艺。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newyorker.com/arts/critics/cinema/2009/08/24/090824crci_cinema_denby|title=Americans in Paris|first=David|last=Denby|work=[[The_New_Yorker|The New Yorker]]|publisher=Condé Nast Publications|date=2009-08-24|accessdate=2010-05-23|archive-date=2010-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100319223742/http://www.newyorker.com/arts/critics/cinema/2009/08/24/090824crci_cinema_denby|dead-url=no}}</ref>”[[克里斯托弗·希欽斯|克里斯托弗·希欽斯]]把观影经历比作“坐在黑暗中让一壶热尿非常缓慢地倒在你头上”<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thepunch.com.au/articles/interview-christopher-hitchens/asc/|title=Interview: Christopher Hitchens|last=Clayfield|first=Matthew|date=2009-10-03|work=[[The_Punch_(Australia)|The Punch]]|publisher=[[News_Limited|News Limited]]|accessdate=2012-03-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121230185139/http://www.thepunch.com.au/articles/interview-christopher-hitchens/asc|archive-date=2012-12-30|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。

本片也受到了一些犹太媒体的批评。在《药片》（{{lang|en|''Tablet''}}）中，里尔·利波韦茨（{{lang|en|Liel Liebowitz}}）批评本片缺乏道德深度。他认为电影的力量来自于它传达的知识和微妙的理解，但《无耻混蛋》更像是“现实的替换物，一个神奇的、[[摩尼教|摩尼教]]式的世界，在其中不用担心道德的复杂性，暴力可以解决一切问题，而[[第三帝国|第三帝国]]的结局只是一堆胶片和一根点燃的火柴造成的卡通片式的战败”<ref name="Tablet">{{cite web|url=http://www.tabletmag.com/arts-and-culture/14057/inglorious-indeed/|title=Inglorious Indeed|last=Leibovitz|first=Liel|date=2009-08-21|work=Tablet Magazine|publisher=Nextbook|accessdate=September 9, 2009<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nFhtc4U4 |archivedate=February 2, 2010 -->|archive-date=2011-09-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110918085153/http://www.tabletmag.com/arts-and-culture/14057/inglorious-indeed/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。网络杂志《{{lang|en|Galus Australi}}》的作者安东尼·弗洛什（{{lang|en|Anthony Frosh}}）批评本片没有塑造好角色，称该电影“迷人，但缺乏犹太人的内容”<ref>{{cite web|url=http://galusaustralis.com/2009/09/inglourious-basterds-enthralling-but-lacking-in-jewish-content/|title=Inglourious Basterds Enthralling But Lacking In Jewish Content|author=Frosh, Anthony|work=Galus Australis|date=2009-09-29|accessdate=January 19, 2010<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nFi1OnHE |archivedate=February 2, 2010 -->|archive-date=2021-04-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210420201820/http://galusaustralis.com/2009/09/inglourious-basterds-enthralling-but-lacking-in-jewish-content/}}</ref>。

== 荣誉 ==
[[克里斯托弗·瓦尔兹|克里斯多夫·華茲]]收获了本片唯一的[[坎城影展|坎城影展]]荣誉——[[最佳男演員獎_(坎城影展)|最佳男演员奖]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Best Actor to Christoph Waltz for his role in "Inglourious Basterds"|url=http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/theDailyArticle/56830.html|publisher=Cannes Festival|date=2009-05-24|accessdate=August 21, 2009<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nFiQrAXG|archivedate=February 2, 2010 -->|archive-url=https://archive.is/20100118134058/http://www.festival-cannes.com/en/theDailyArticle/56830.html|archive-date=2010-01-18|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。影评人德温·法拉希（{{lang|en|Devin Faraci}}）说：“在这篇影评写就的很久之前就已产生了这样的呼声，但让我来继续呼吁吧：[[克里斯托弗·瓦尔兹|克里斯多夫·華茲]]不需要一个奥斯卡提名，而是真正地拿到这个奖项……他必须赢得小金人”<ref>{{cite web|author=Faraci, Devin|title=Inglourious Basterds|url=http://chud.com/articles/articles/20501/1/REVIEW-INGLOURIOUS-BASTERDS/Page1.html|publisher=Chud.com|date=2009-08-18|accessdate=August 20, 2009<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nFiTiIh6|archivedate=February 2, 2010 -->|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090820191030/http://chud.com/articles/articles/20501/1/REVIEW-INGLOURIOUS-BASTERDS/Page1.html|archive-date=2009-08-20|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。本电影获得了4项[[金球奖|金球奖]]提名<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/12/16/movies/awardsseason/16globes.html|title='Up in the Air' Nominated for 6 Golden Globes|work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|publisher=The New York Times Company|first=Brooks|last=Barnes|date=2009-12-15|accessdate=January 26, 2010<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nFiWZIoF |archivedate=February 2, 2010 -->|archive-date=2018-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180617165253/https://www.nytimes.com/2009/12/16/movies/awardsseason/16globes.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>，包括[[金球獎最佳戲劇類影片|最佳戲劇類影片]]提名和華兹的[[金球獎最佳電影男配角|最佳電影男配角]]提名，他最终获得了该奖项<ref>{{cite web|url=http://screencrave.com/2010-01-17/golden-globes-2010-winner-for-best-supporting-actor/|title=Golden Globes 2010: Christoph Waltz Wins for Best Supporting Actor|work=Screen Crave|date=2010-01-17|accessdate=January 26, 2010<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nFiZFDDt |archivedate=February 2, 2010 -->|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110726072539/http://screencrave.com/2010-01-17/golden-globes-2010-winner-for-best-supporting-actor/|archive-date=2011-07-26|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。本片也获得了3项[[美国演员工会奖|美国演员工会奖]]提名，并最终获得了{{link-en|最佳整體演出|Screen Actors Guild Award for Outstanding Performance by a Cast in a Motion Picture}}和[[美国演员工会奖最佳男配角|最佳男配角奖]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/8476830.stm|title=Inglourious Basterds Wins Top Screen Actors Guild Award|work=[[BBC_News|BBC News]]|date=2010-01-24|accessdate=January 24, 2010<!-- |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5nFibot3H|archivedate=February 2, 2010 -->|archive-date=2010-02-02|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5nFibot3H?url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/8476830.stm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。本片获得了[[英國電影學院獎|英國電影學院獎]]的6项提名，包括塔伦蒂诺的最佳导演提名<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=26778|title=BAFTA Nominations 2010 Announced!|work=[[Empire_(magazine)|Empire]]|publisher=Bauer Consumer Media|date=2010-01-12|accessdate=2010-02-10|archive-date=2012-01-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120122164203/http://www.empireonline.com/news/story.asp?NID=26778|dead-url=no}}</ref>，但只赢得了一项——華兹的[[英國電影學院獎最佳男配角|最佳男配角]]奖。在2010年2月的[[第82届奥斯卡奖|第82届奥斯卡奖]]上，《无耻混蛋》得到了8项提名，包括[[奥斯卡最佳影片奖|最佳影片]]、[[奥斯卡最佳导演奖|最佳导演]]、[[奥斯卡最佳男配角奖|最佳男配角]]、[[奥斯卡最佳原创剧本奖|最佳原创剧本]]、[[奧斯卡最佳攝影獎|最佳摄影]]、[[奥斯卡最佳剪辑奖|最佳剪辑]]、[[奥斯卡最佳音效剪辑奖|最佳音效剪辑]]和[[奥斯卡最佳混音奖|最佳混音]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oscars.org/awards/academyawards/legacy/ceremony/82nd-winners.html|title=The 82nd Academy Awards (2010) Nominees and Winners|publisher=[[Academy_of_Motion_Picture_Arts_and_Sciences|Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]]|accessdate=2011-11-22|archive-date=2014-10-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006110009/http://www.oscars.org/awards/academyawards/legacy/ceremony/82nd-winners.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。最终華兹获得了[[奥斯卡最佳男配角奖|奥斯卡最佳男配角奖]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2010/03/07/arts/entertainment-us-oscars-waltz.html|title=Christoph Waltz Wins Oscar For "Basterds"|work=The New York Times|publisher=The New York Times Company|first=Alex|last=Dobuzinskis|date=2010-03-07|accessdate=2010-03-08}}{{Dead link}}</ref>。

